.\" ###### Setup ############################################################
.Dd May 9, 2026
.Dt view\-crl 1
.Os view\-crl
.\" ###### Name #############################################################
.Sh NAME
.Nm view\-crl
.Nd displays important details of an X.509 CRL in PEM or DER format
.\" ###### Synopsis #########################################################
.\" Manpage syntax help:
.\" https://forums.freebsd.org/threads/howto-create-a-manpage-from-scratch.13200/
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm view\-crl Ar crl\_file
.Op ...
.Nm view\-crl
.Op Fl h | Fl Fl help
.Nm view\-crl
.Op Fl v | Fl Fl version
.\" ###### Description ######################################################
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm view\-crl
displays important details of an X.509 CRL in PEM or DER format, including the serial numbers and dates of revoked certificates.
.Pp
.\" ###### Arguments ########################################################
.Sh ARGUMENTS
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ar crl\_file ...
Specifies one or more CRL files to be displayed. "\-" is a shortcut for
.Pa /dev/stdin ,
i.e. reading the CRL from standard input.
.It Fl h | Fl Fl help
Prints the program's command\-line parameters and exits.
.It Fl v | Fl Fl version
Prints the program version and exits.
.El
.\" ###### Exit status ######################################################
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
tool exits with 0 on success, and >0 in case of an error.
.\" ###### Examples #########################################################
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It view\-crl My\-CA\-CRL.crl
.It view\-crl /usr/lib/python3.12/test/certdata/revocation.crl
.It curl \-o google\-crl.der.crl http://c.pki.goog/wr2/GSyT1N4PBrg.crl && \
view\-crl google\-crl.der.crl
.It curl \-\-output \- http://c.pki.goog/wr2/GSyT1N4PBrg.crl | view\-crl \-
.It view\-crl \-\-help
.It view\-crl \-h
.It view\-crl \-\-version
.It view\-crl \-v
.El
